Text: In this section, you will be presented with a series of word pairs. As you study, you will be asked to rate your ability to remember the second item in the pair if you were only shown the first at test. You will make these ratings using a 0 to 100 Scale.

For  example, if you are given the pair CAT - DOG, a rating of 0 indicates that you would not remember DOG at test, while a rating of 100 indicates full certainty that you would remember the word DOG at test.

When making these ratings, it is criticial that you use the full range of the scale. You will be disqualified for only giving ratings of 0 or 100! After making your rating, press Enter to advance to the next pair.

As you study and make your ratings, please think about how the two concepts are RELATED to each other. For example, if you see the pair TURTLE-CAT, think about how both are alive, they are both animals, and both can be kept as pets.
What you should think about as you study each item pair? Type your response in the box below.

The order that words are presented in can affect how well you remember them. For example, the pairs CREDIT-CARD and CARD-CREDIT both have the same words, but people are less likely to remember backward pairs like CARD-CREDIT because the order is uncommon. On the next screen you will be shown a graph illustrating this finding. Please study it for at least 20 seconds.
Based on the graph you just studied, what pair type is best remembered (Forward, Backward, or Symmetrical)?
You will now be presented with a new set of word pairs. Please study each pair. Remember that your memory will be tested! When finished, press Enter to move to the next pair.
You will again be asked to rate your ability to remember these items using a 0 to 100 scale. Remember to use the full range of the scale!
